I haven&#x27;t seen the code, obviously, but Minecraft has a lot of functionality similar to cellular automata. That is, checking the contents of adjacent cells.<p>I imagine the code went from<p><pre><code>  v1 = Cell.testPos(x-1,y,z);
  v2 = Cell.testPos(x+1,y,z);
  v3 = Cell.testPos(x,y-1,z);
  ...
</code></pre>
To<p><pre><code>  v1 = Cell.testPos(new BlockPos(block.x-1,block.y,block.z));
  v2 = Cell.testPos(new BlockPos(block.x+1,block.y,block.z));
  v3 = Cell.testPos(new BlockPos(block.x,block.y-1,block.z));
  ...</code></pre>
